<h2>Key points</h2>
<ul>
<li>A chest tube is inserted between the ribs to drain fluid or air from the pleural space.</li>
<li>The tube can be placed in the chest using ultrasound and X-ray guidance.</li>
<li>Usually, chest tube insertion is a low-risk procedure.</li>
<li>Removing the chest tube is usually done at the bedside without anaesthetic.</li>
</ul>
