<h2>Risks of chest tube insertion</h2>
<p>Chest tube insertion is usually considered a low-risk procedure. The risk may increase depending on your child's condition, age and health.</p>
<p>The risks of a chest tube insertion include:</p>
<ul>
<li>pain or discomfort</li>
<li>leakage of air back into the pleural space</li>
<li>infection</li>
<li>worsening breathing problems</li>
</ul>
<p><br/></p> </div>
</div>
